http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Modi-to-open-Paradip-refinery/article13988382.ece

Prime Minister Narendra Modi will be on a two-day visit to Odisha from February 6 and inaugurate the 15 MMTPA Paradip refinery of Indian Oil Corporation on the first day.Giving this information to the media here on Thursday, Union Petroleum and Natural Gas Minister Dharmendra Pradhan said that Mr. Modi will also visit Jagannath temple in Puri on February.The foundation stone for the Paradip refinery was laid by the then Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee in May 2000. With a project cost of Rs. 34,555 crore, the Paradip refinery will be the most modern refinery in India with a nil-residue production.On the second day of his visit, Mr. Modi is scheduled to inaugurate the permanent campus of the National Institute of Science Education and Research (NISER) at Jatni near Bhubaneswar.